Description:
Rare - Unique - Fine Country Living
Take advantage of this rare opportunity to own a property that is currently operating as a fodder farm/ lifestyle block in one of the best positions in the area. This 85 acre Cobram East property oozes charm & comfort for that country living lifestyle. It is sure to impress.
Boasting a lovely rural outlook, this brick veneer home features vast improvements with recent renovations. The four bedroom plus study home features a contemporary classic style kitchen including a brand new induction cooktop and 900mm electric oven and a brand new Meile dishwasher, a large butlers pantry, open living and dining area; four good sized bedrooms all with built in wardrobes & main with walk-in-robe and ensuite.
This light filled home has two stylish outdoor areas with large bullnose verandas. Beautiful neutral colour pallet throughout with spotted gum floating timber flooring. Offering for comfort and convenience, this home is sure to keep you warm during the colder months with the American Lopi wood heater with electric start for convenience on those cool nights and there is three split systems that will keep you warm or cool all year round. There is ceiling fans throughout.
This beautiful property is set up to cater to your four-legged friends if you like. The 85 acres is divided into numerous tree lined paddocks with padman stops to flood irrigate the pastures. All the paddocks can be accessed from the well maintained laneways. There is stock yards, horse stables and tack room, machinery sheds and workshop with concrete floor.
The property offers stock and domestic bore; water tanks; padman stops; recently new fencing including electric; plenty of shedding; 12 meg recycle dam; an artist studio or storage shed and gravelled driveway.
The property comprises of permanent pastures- Lucerne, permanent rye grass and sown to oats & rye & shaftel yearly with great results for making hay. 90% of the farm can be flood irrigated directly off the main channel. Currently running 40 cows & calves
All only 8 minutes from the heart of Cobram on a sealed road, with school bus available.
Be quick as these properties don't last long! Arrange an inspection today!

Description:
LIFESTYLE / HOBBY FARM WITH BEAUTIFUL 4 BEDROOM HOME SET ON 4 ACRES
Phone enquiries - please quote property ID 23411
This lifestyle property has so many things to offer and is sure to impress. The property is ideal for horses, farm animals or vegetation. It is situated just 8 minutes drive into Cobram,20 minutes to Yarrawonga and approximately 2.5 hours from Melbourne.
THE HOME
This quality home was built by Brian Hyde some 14 years ago. It is beautifully maintained inside and out. The home is well set back from the road with access via a gravel driveway. It has all the comforts needed for your country home life, with spacious, open plan living, dining and kitchen areas as well as a 6 metre x 6 metre sun room which provides extra year round living. There are 4 bedrooms in total. The master bedroom has a walk in robe and en suite. The 3 remaining bedrooms have large built in robes. 2 easily accommodate queen size beds, the other is still of generous proportions and is currently being utilised as a study. The home has reverse cycle air-conditioning and ceiling fans throughout. There is a wood fire in the living area which heats the entire house.
Attached is a double garage with a remote control door and access directly into the sun room.
Verandas surround the house and have roll down mesh sun blinds along the front veranda extending over the sliding glass doors of the sun room.
LAND AND OTHER IMPROVEMENTS
The entire property is fully fenced and includes 7 paddocks with electric fencing, 6 of these have automatically filled water troughs and irrigation points.The garden areas around the house have manicured lawns and beautiful trees. Most of the garden areas are irrigated.
Towards the rear of the property is a large shed measuring 20 metres x 8 metres. It incorporates a concrete floored work shop, a very large secured area suitable for storing cars, caravans, tractors etc and another room that would be suitable as a rumpus room ,games room or gym. It has a concrete floor with a vinyl plank overlay. The roof of the shed accommodates 20 solar panels. The properties water is supplied via a bore and water tank. The septic tank has a bio system which also provides some of the ground watering. There is also a large chook pen, raised vegetable garden beds and other small shedding. The land is level and easy to maintain.
This wonderful property is now on the market. Highly recommended for your viewing.

Description:
Outstanding Irrigation ~ Lifestyle Property
53 Acres (21.44 Ha)
$730,000 + Water at market value
Executive Home
Industrial Shed
Lucerne ~ Horses ~ Stud Stock

This 53 acre property has a craftsman-built home that features a well appointed kitchen/dining room with plenty of cupboards, separate lounge, rumpus/billiard room with cathedral ceilings and a built in bar. Four generous bedrooms, three with built in robes, main with an ensuite and walk in robe. Large enclosed undercover entertaining area with a built in barbecue. Ducted evaporative cooling, floor heating and ducted vacuum system. Double garage under roofline with an extra toilet. Massive 60 x 40 foot shed (approx.) that includes a self contained unit and a skillion for extra machinery. Excellent paddock structure with water troughs, fencing, cattle yards, loading race, large hay shed, and a stand area to suite B double trucks.

Description:
PART NIRRUNGA DAIRIES - LIFESTYLE - DAIRY HORTICULTURE FODDER IRRIGATION - LIVESTOCK
Situated in the tightly held Cobram East district, 'Nirrunga Dairies' presents prospective purchasers with an excellent opportunity to secure proven Cobram loam and Cobram sandy loam soils with excellent surface and ground water supply. The property aggregation comprises of 3 titles which can be purchased individually or in any combination. A brief description of the three landholdings (titles) are set out below.
Lot 1) Part 606 Healy Road, Cobram East - 50.41 hectares / 124.56 acres (UNDER CONTRACT)
*Comprising of Cobram sandy loam & Cobram loam soils this property has been recently developed for fast efficient flood irrigation.
*Connected to Goulburn Murray Water and featuring one irrigation delivery point and a stock & domestic connection.
*Spear point (electric) irrigation bore including 306ML Water Entitlements.
*Working improvements include a hay shed, pressurised stock trough system, formed laneway/internal roadways.
*A well presented property with established treeline plantations and an exceptional pasture and fertiliser history. Soil types are ideally suited to high returning horticultural crops.
Lot 2) Part 606 Healy Road, Cobram East - 37.90 hectares / 93.65 acres (UNDER CONTRACT)
*A proven irrigation property featuring established treeline plantations, formed laneway/internal roadways.
*Exceptional irrigation development with recycle system, quality channel infrastructure and bay outlets.
*A well presented property with exceptional pasture and fertiliser history and currently presents with annual pastures of Italian rye grass & Shaftal clover.
*Working improvements include a set of steel cattle yards with loading facilities and a pressurised stock trough system.
Lot 3) 277 Cottons Road, Cobram East - 15.61 hectares / 38.57 acres (UNDER CONTRACT)
*Three bedroom, two bathroom weatherboard home featuring split systems, 2 bay carport, mixed shedding and a stock and domestic bore.
*Predominantly lasered border check irrigation with one GMW delivery point.
*Currently presents with annual pastures of Italian rye grass & Shaftal clover.
*An excellent lifestyle or small farm opportunity within close proximity to Cobram via sealed roads.
Agents Comments: 606 Healy Road Cobram East is an outstanding dairy operation with prime arable soils, excellent water and providing the opportunity to diversify into alternative agriculture and horticultural pursuits. A substantial water portfolio is also attached to the landholdings and available by negotiation. For further details, contact Matt Horne of Elders on 0409 355 733.

Description:
118.5 Ha - Superbly Managed & Developed
Offered for sale the second time in over 30 years, the property is an absolute credit to the vendors. Basically fully laser graded to a farm plan, full water reticulation, all new fencing & excellent laneways. Freshly sown & watered, the property is ready for the coming season. The homestead comprises 4 bedrooms with ensuite & WIR to main, open plan living, air conditioning etc. The modern dairy is 15 S/O, 10,000 ltr vat, 300 cow yard & 32 tonne silo cap plus 9 tonne pellet silo. 2 mach sheds, 2 haysheds.
3.5 GMW delivery shares, 306 ML shallow bore licence (not currently operational) plus 173 ML high security & 106 Ml low security waterright available at current valuation.
Currently milking 150 milkers (av 600 kgs MS) plus carrying 64 hfrs & 57 yrlgs, all available at valuation.
One of the better properties offered for sale in a long time, inspect with confidence.

Description:
160 Acres - Water Views - River Access - Bush Setting
Rare water front land situated between Cobram and Yarrawonga beside the Mighty Murray River. 160 acres currently under orchard (including cherries). It has several excellent home sites with water frontage. (STCA) Fronts state forest with a small beach and boat access to the Murray River. Create your dream here! Irrigation water on the property with 320 megalitres from spear point and 158 megalitre delivery share from the creek with pump. Irrigation pipes throughout the property. Possible subdivision potential (STCA). Excellent soils. Keep the orchard for some income or lifestyle block, hobby farm. Choices galore. A rare opportunity to purchase a waterfront property.
